div.div:
Implement inter-chain bond handling and structure cleaning in the pipeline
- Added inter_chain_bonds.py to manage polymer-ligand and ligand-ligand bond extraction. - Introduced functions to retrieve bond atom arrays and filter bonds based on specified criteria. - Enhanced pipeline.py to integrate inter-chain bond features into the data processing workflow. - Developed structure_cleaning.py to prepare PDB structures for training, including filtering and cleaning operations. - Implemented mechanisms to handle leaving atoms and manage bond types effectively. - Added error handling for data integrity checks during processing.

Refactor DNA flexibility analysis module and enhance notebook documentation
- Simplified the flexibility analysis by removing the FlexibilityAnalyzer class and introducing a standalone function. - Updated the Jupyter notebook to include comprehensive examples for DNA flexibility and structural analysis. - Improved requirements file to ensure compatibility with updated libraries. - Added extensive unit tests for atom layout functionality, covering initialization, validation, indexing, and specific features for DNA and protein layouts.
feat: Implement atom type classifications and structure analysis functions

Add AtomLayout and Residues classes for structure representation
- Implemented AtomLayout class to manage atom layouts with fixed shapes. - Created Residues class to handle residue metadata including deprotonation and SMILES strings. - Added utility functions for converting between atom layouts and structures. - Introduced gather indices computation for translating between layouts. - Updated tests for protein model tokenization and embedding generation to validate new structures. - Configured VSCode settings for pytest integration. - Added initial tools module for future utility functions.
